    <string name="help_old_school"><![CDATA[<h2>Hints</h2>
    <p>In the old school mode, you can let the CPU <b>guess</b> one character for you.</p>
    <p>When a hint/guess is placed, it makes the respective button of the keyboard <b>yellow</b>.</p>
    <p>Now you have to <em>acknowledge</em> the guess by pressing that button.</p>
    <p>This will also ensure that any other letters in the word with the hint letter is also filled up.</p>]]></string>

    <string name="help_genre"><![CDATA[<h2>Hints</h2>
    <p>In genre mode, instead of guessing the character, you will be shown a hint from where you have to guess the word!</p>
    <p>It could be a <b>quote</b> from a movie or even a <b>riddle</b> for you to solve!</p>]]></string>

    <string name="help"><![CDATA[<p></p>
    <p>Hangman is a game of guessing words. Try to guess the word by guessing each letter.</p>
    <p>Read more in the Wikipedia <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hangman_(game)">article</a></p>
    <p>With every wrong guess, the stick figure gets closer to getting hanged! <b>Save him!</b></p>
    <p>Make sure that <b>"hangman"</b> is not hanged!</p>
    <p><b>May the guess be with you!</b></p>]]></string>

